00:32:21.040 --> 00:32:23.040
Okay, the third concept.

00:32:23.040 --> 00:32:30.040
So there are certain statistical transformations that you can do using PlotMine.

00:32:30.040 --> 00:32:36.040
Think about grouping or counting things.

00:32:36.040 --> 00:32:39.040
This is quite convenient.

00:32:39.040 --> 00:32:45.040
So what I'm doing right here is I'm using the function geomhistograph.

00:32:46.040 --> 00:32:55.040
And what's interesting to note is that I am not explicitly specifying this count column.

00:32:55.040 --> 00:32:57.040
You see this here on the left.

00:32:57.040 --> 00:33:06.040
Notice, by the way, that this is so natural to me.

00:33:07.040 --> 00:33:15.040
Can we just appreciate for a second how many things PlotMine does for you out of the box?

00:33:15.040 --> 00:33:19.040
You've got your limits all set up based on the data.

00:33:19.040 --> 00:33:21.040
You've got your labels.

00:33:21.040 --> 00:33:24.040
You've got default colors.

00:33:24.040 --> 00:33:28.040
And so lots of legend.

00:33:28.040 --> 00:33:31.040
Lots of sensible defaults.

00:33:31.040 --> 00:33:38.040
And it is good to know that each of these can be overwritten.

00:33:38.040 --> 00:33:40.040
You want the colors to be different.

00:33:40.040 --> 00:33:42.040
You want the font to be different.

00:33:42.040 --> 00:33:44.040
Everything.

00:33:44.040 --> 00:33:48.040
But right now we're still creating these quick data visualizations.

00:33:48.040 --> 00:33:53.040
So with geomhistogram, it's a bunch of bars.

00:33:53.040 --> 00:33:58.040
But what is happening under the hood is that there's also some counting going on.

00:33:58.040 --> 00:34:08.040
And so PlotMine creates this new column for us, count, which gets mapped to the y-aesthetic.

00:34:08.040 --> 00:34:17.040
So it's a bit confusing, but notice that the y-column is actually mapped to the x-aesthetic.

00:34:17.040 --> 00:34:21.040
Just to make things more confusing.

00:34:21.040 --> 00:34:25.040
So this is conceptually what is going on under the hood.

00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:31.040
You provide it with a data frame, but before PlotMine actually visualizes everything,

00:34:31.040 --> 00:34:36.040
it furnishes us some, in this case, a group-by operation.

00:34:39.040 --> 00:34:41.040
And this is optional.

00:34:41.040 --> 00:34:47.040
When all the data that you're using for visualization is already in the data frame,

00:34:47.040 --> 00:34:49.040
then this is optional.

00:34:49.040 --> 00:34:55.040
And you are still free to do any of these aggregations yourself.

00:34:55.040 --> 00:35:02.040
If you have prepared the data frame in such a way that it can be immediately used to create a histogram,

00:35:02.040 --> 00:35:06.040
or a density plot, or a box plot, that works too.

