you can map the value

00:56:40.040 --> 00:56:41.040
of the variable

00:56:41.040 --> 00:56:43.040
to the value of the color.

00:56:43.040 --> 00:56:44.040
Yeah.

00:56:44.040 --> 00:56:46.040
If I can summarize your question,

00:56:46.040 --> 00:56:48.040
let me know if I got it wrong,

00:56:48.040 --> 00:56:49.040
is that, okay,

00:56:49.040 --> 00:56:50.040
how can you be certain

00:56:50.040 --> 00:56:51.040
that a specific value

00:56:51.040 --> 00:56:53.040
gets mapped to a specific color

00:56:53.040 --> 00:56:55.040
and then specifically

00:56:55.040 --> 00:56:57.040
for multiple

00:56:57.040 --> 00:56:59.040
data visualization?

00:56:59.040 --> 00:57:00.040
Yeah, I mean,

00:57:00.040 --> 00:57:01.040
for one,

00:57:02.040 --> 00:57:04.040
what I typically do

00:57:04.040 --> 00:57:06.040
is I create

00:57:06.040 --> 00:57:08.040
another column in my data frame

00:57:08.040 --> 00:57:10.040
with the color name

00:57:10.040 --> 00:57:12.040
or even perhaps a code.

00:57:12.040 --> 00:57:14.040
And then you can use

00:57:14.040 --> 00:57:17.040
the function scaleColorIdentity.

00:57:17.040 --> 00:57:19.040
And then your aesthetic mapping

00:57:19.040 --> 00:57:21.040
becomes color

00:57:21.040 --> 00:57:22.040
or fill

00:57:22.040 --> 00:57:23.040
equals

00:57:23.040 --> 00:57:25.040
the name of the column

00:57:25.040 --> 00:57:26.040
that you chose.

00:57:26.040 --> 00:57:27.040
So it's color equals color.

00:57:27.040 --> 00:57:28.040
Right?

00:57:28.040 --> 00:57:30.040
So maybe it's cheating,

00:57:30.040 --> 00:57:32.040
but you're embedding

00:57:32.040 --> 00:57:34.040
visualization data

00:57:34.040 --> 00:57:36.040
in your data frame.

00:57:36.040 --> 00:57:37.040
But then at least,

00:57:37.040 --> 00:57:39.040
well, I can be certain

00:57:39.040 --> 00:57:41.040
that the mapping is always

00:57:41.040 --> 00:57:43.040
the same.

00:57:43.040 --> 00:57:44.040
But there's no API

00:57:44.040 --> 00:57:46.040
like scaleColorManualIdentity.

00:57:46.040 --> 00:57:47.040
On top of that,

00:57:47.040 --> 00:57:48.040
you can tell also

00:57:48.040 --> 00:57:49.040
the mapping

00:57:49.040 --> 00:57:50.040
values of the color

00:57:50.040 --> 00:57:52.040
and the name.

00:57:52.040 --> 00:57:53.040
And it breaks.

00:57:53.040 --> 00:57:55.040
I think it breaks in values.

00:57:57.040 --> 00:57:59.040
Oh, so you're...

00:58:00.040 --> 00:58:02.040
Yeah, so in this...

00:58:06.040 --> 00:58:08.040
Right, so in this example here,

